Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Assistant Library Director Chetwnd , BC Description Mission: To look out into our community and see a reflection of our outstanding services. Vision: To encourage strong community partnerships, provide diverse programs with flexible services that bring people together and foster individual creativity. Job posting for: Assistant Library Director The Chetwynd Public Library is looking for a personable, charismatic, outgoing individual that has drive and passion for community and excellent customer service skills. This role requires a customer-focused individual who values the importance of creating a welcoming library experience. The ideal candidate will actively listen to patrons and address their needs. The Assistant Library Director is a vital member of the library's leadership team. They work closely with the Library Director in aligning the library with its strategic plan. The roll of the Assistant Library Director includes, but is not limited to community outreach, grant applications, reporting, programming, events, advertising, marketing, website, and social media posts. Do you enjoy: keeping up with technological changes and trends, innovative programs, and community engagement? If you are an enthusiastic individual with a love for libraries and lifelong learning, a commitment to community-driven initiatives, and a desire to contribute to the future of library services, we encourage you to apply for this position. Join our dedicated team and help us create a dynamic and inclusive library environment that meets the evolving needs of our community. Responsibilities: Collaborates with the Library Director and other team members to develop and execute a strategic vision that aligns with the library's future-focused and community-driven mission.Searches for and applies for external funding with grants and donations.Reports monthly on programming, verbal and written.Assists in the reviewing, writing, and maintaining of policies and procedures. Keeps resources, both online and in-house, up to date. Primary editor of the website and social media.Assists with library on location and provides support and back-up for library programming.Ensures that the library system complies with all relevant workplace safety and labour requirements.Stays current with emerging trends and technologies in library science and related fields to enhance library offerings and optimize user experience. Assists in staff management and human resources as assigned by the Library Director, by providing leadership and guidance to library staff, promoting teamwork, professional development, and a culture of excellence.Collaborates with community organizations, local government, schools, and other stakeholders to establish partnerships, identify opportunities for collaboration, and support community engagement. Conducts regular assessments and evaluations including statistical information to measure the library's impact, gather feedback, and inform the decision-making processes. Acts as a representative of the library at community events, conferences, and meetings. Please note that the responsibilities and qualifications outlined in this job description are intended to provide an overview of the main duties and requirements of the position. It is not exhaustive and may be subject to change based on the needs of the library. Qualifications and attributes: Master’s degree in library science, information science or five+ years of experience in related capacity such as a public or academic library or alternatively in an office or public service organization that had provided experience in transferable skills.Website and social media certification or two+ years relevant experience.Communication courses and or relevant experience in a leadership role, mentoring and guiding others.Knowledgeable of non-profit organizations, and libraries.An understanding and commitment to the principles of inclusiveness and service excellence.Excellent interpersonal and communication skills, with the ability to effectively engage with diverse audiences, build community partnerships, and apply a range of communication styles to effectively transfer thoughts and ideas.Empathetic, patient approach in interacting with patrons of all ages and setting professional boundaries.High level of judgment and excellent problem-solving skills.Demonstrated level of professionalism and confidentiality with strong ethics.Demonstrated team-building abilities, fostering a collaborative and inclusive work environment.Commitment to fostering diversity, equity, and inclusion in library services and programs.Strong organizational skills, with the ability to prioritize and manage multiple projects and initiatives simultaneously. A forward-thinking mindset with a passion for exploring emerging technologies, digital literacy, and innovative library services. Flexibility and adaptability to thrive in a fast-paced and evolving library environment through changing business needs, conditions, and work responsibilities. A strong understanding of library operations, policies, and procedures is an asset. We are willing to train the right individual and look forward to having you join our library team. Compensation: Permanent full-time, 35 hours per week (may include evenings and weekends based on library programming) Wage $26.79-$28.13 Benefits including Medical, Dental, Extended Health and Municipal Pension Plan Application Instructions: Email application to mmillsap@chetwyndpubliclibrary.ca Fax to 250-788-2186 or drop off at 5012 46th street, Chetwynd, BC For more information, please call 250-788-2559 Please submit or email the following documents with the subject line "Assistant Library Director Application." A comprehensive resume highlighting your relevant experience and qualifications. A cover letter expressing your interest in the position and outlining how your skills and experience align with the library's mission and vision. Contact information for three professional references. Applications will be accepted until Sunday July 23, 2023, with an anticipated start date of the beginning of August. We thank and appreciate all those who apply, please be advised that only those shortlisted for an interview will be contacted. Compensation $26.79-$28.13 Closes: 23 July, 2023 Chetwynd Public Library Chetwnd , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
