als in and out of the system, including using automated tools. Sorts, shelves and cleans library materialsDesigns and prepares a variety of visual media e.g., displays, signage, etc., and promotes library services, initiatives and merchandiseRecommends materials for the library collection, including online resourcesPrepares reports, statistics or other documents Participating in collection maintenance duties, eg. shelf reading and weeding Keeps library in neat and orderly conditionPerforms other related dutiesQualifications, Knowledge, and Skills Diploma in Library Technology from a recognized Library Technician’s program, or an equivalent combination of directly related work experience, training and courses Accurate keyboarding speed of 35 words per minute 1 to 2 years working experience providing customer service in a public service environment Knowledge of Library’s policies and operations Knowledge of library resources and collection, as related to the work performed Knowledge of programming techniques and materials Knowledge of computer hardware and software applications related to the work performed Ability to communicate effectively, spoken and written Ability to serve the public courteously and effectively and maintain good working relationships with other staff Ability to meet physical demands of the work including safe handling of materials Ability to work in a fast-paced and stressful environment Oral fluency in another language is an asset, particularly Arabic, Spanish, Asian or South Asian languagesYouth Services education and/or experience is an asset How to apply A criminal record check, with no conviction of any offence related to the position applied for, is a condition of employment. If you are interested in this opportunity, send your cover letter, resume and unofficial transcript with the subject “Casual Public Services Technician” to SPLEmployment@surrey.ca. The deadline is July 20, 2023. We thank in advance all applicants who apply and advise that only those selected for testing or interviewing will be contacted Compensation $32.61-$33.48 Closes: 20 July, 2023 Surrey Libraries Surrey , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
