Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Information Resources &amp; Connections Data Analyst Associate Niagara Falls , ON Description Information Resources &amp; Connections Data Analyst AssociateNiagara Falls Public LibraryFixed-Term, Full-Time (12 Month Contract)Niagara Falls Public Library is seeking a full-time temporary data analyst associate. The successful candidate will be someone who shares our vision for integrity, collaboration, creativity, and respect. Working with the IRC Librarian and IT team, the incumbent of this position will support the Niagara Falls Public Library’s (NFPL) strategic goal to make data-informed decisions about its resources and collections.The successful candidate will be part of a diverse, multidisciplinary team where communication and teamwork are critical, and novel solutions are encouraged.As a Data Analyst, you will contribute to the organization's success by performing data analysis using open-source tools and modern techniques. You will collect, organise and evaluate data to assist the IRC Librarian on collections-based library projects and purchasing decisions. You will also support the IT department in determining organizational needs, troubleshooting technological issues, and monitoring systems.Key Responsibilities:Extracts and analyzes data from different sources including databases, cataloguing records, and information systems.Formulates relevant queries within BI platforms.Prepares and organizes statistics, reports and dashboards to make key data available to assist decision-making. Works with the IRC librarian to come up with data necessary to inform purchasing decisions, right-sizing of the collection, DEI collection initiatives, and other similar collections-based library projects.Communicates with the IRC department to determine what reports are necessary and what data must be extracted and analyzed.Supports the IT department in determining organizational needs, troubleshooting technological issues, and monitoring systems.Stays abreast of Library communications.Shares accountability for ensuring a safe and respectful workplace.Other duties consistent with job responsibilities.Skills, Knowledge, Training:A post-secondary diploma in computer science, data analytics or a related field from a recognized post-secondary institution or an equivalent combination of education and experience.Demonstrated understanding of data analysis, database management and business intelligence concepts.Experience working with data in various formats and with various data analysis tools / business intelligence platforms, particularly open source software. An ability to identify patterns, trends, and anomalies in data, and to provide insights that support decision-making processes.Demonstrated familiarity writing SQL queries to extract and analyze data.A keen analytical mindset and ability to solve complex problems with a systematic and logical approach.Demonstrated familiarity with current technology and general troubleshooting knowledge are considered an asset.Library experience is an asset.Key Competencies:Commitment to outstanding customer serviceProblem solving and decision makingStrong communicationsStrong interpersonal skillsContinuous learningPlanning and organizationData AnalysisInnovativeness and Change ManagementTechnology Level 4Workplace Environment:The NFPL strives to be a workplace which fosters respect for all customers and co-workers, and requires employee commitment to the following:Adherence to the legal requirements of all levels of government, e.g. Health and Safety, Human Rights, Harassment, Freedom of Information and Privacy.Adherence to the policies and procedures of the Library which implement these requirements.Building and nurturing positive relationships among and with customers and colleagues.Culture of teamwork, collaboration and respectful feedback.Position Type:Fixed-Term (12 Months), Full-TimeWage:$24.58 per hourWork Hours: 35 hours per week (includes days, evenings and weekends)How to Apply:Email your cover letter and resume detailing your qualifications to hr@nflibrary.ca Applications will be accepted until 4:30 PM, July 21, 2023. Applicants must be eligible to work in Canada.While we appreciate all applicants, only those selected for an interview will be contacted.The Niagara Falls Library is committed to providing accommodations in all aspects of the recruitment and hiring process under the Ontario Human Rights Code and the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act (AODA). Compensation 24.58 Closes: 21 July, 2023 Niagara Falls Public Library Niagara Falls , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
