Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Operations &amp; Records Management Specialist Burnaby , BC Description Who We AreAt BCIT, putting people at the core of everything we do is paramount. This idea is the foundation of BCIT’s People Vision, which describes the Institute’s goals and priorities in respect to our people. In a complex and uncertain world, it’s vital our people feel valued, supported and connected. BCIT champions a culture of innovation and global progress through people’s imagination and creativity. With a competitive compensation package, great work-life balance, and career advancement opportunities, see why we’ve earned the title of one of BC’s Top Employers for over ten years running.Position SummaryBCIT’s Library Services department is seeking a regular, full-time (1.0 FTE) Operations &amp; Records Management Specialist. In support of the Operations Manager and the Director, Library Services, the Operations &amp; Records Management Specialist provides confidential administrative, financial and logistical support for operational matters on all campus libraries. The Operations &amp; Records Management Specialist also provides assistance in information services, including Records Management, Copyright, and Reference.DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:Administrative and Operational Support:Maintains an awareness of the Manager’s and the Director’s goals and objectives, establishing priorities and identifying items requiring attention.Provides administrative and logistical support for all meetings attended by the Director, including taking minutes and arranging speakers.Supports employee engagement by maintaining online presence of activities. Helps with planning and reporting out of engagement activities.Creates content for internal Library operational Loop group.Assists with budget analysis, tracks financial transactions, and expenditure commitments. Initiates expense cross-charges and communicates with Finance Services department.Collects and reports out on revenue, expense and year-to-date transaction reports.Reconciles and submits monthly Purchase Card statements.Conducts walk-throughs to ensure that cleaning standards are maintained and building deficiencies are reported and addressed by Facilities Services department.Coordinates submissions of requisitions for furniture, equipment, supplies, systems, and maintenance contracts. Oversees delivery logistics to ensure timely building access, parking, and installation as required.Ensures Library attendance recording follows Institute policy. Inputs attendance records, reports sick leave deductions to Payroll department, reviews reports with Manager, and submits year-end approved reports to Human Resources department.Supports recruitment by scheduling interviews, preparing interview packages, and booking meeting rooms. Initiates e-hires as required.Coordinates telecommunication requests to Information Technology Services (ITS).Coordinates security access rights.Prepares and maintains Library statistics for provincial and national surveys.Act as the Records Custodian of the Library Services Administration office. Annually reviews, creates and discards files according to Records Management policy and procedures.Information Services:Reference:Responds to inquiries at the Research Help Desk. Assists patrons to find resources for their research. Refers questions that require subject matter expertise or further consultation to librarians.Maintains current knowledge of reference tools and resources through in-house and external continuing education opportunities.Records Management:Liaise with ITS for troubleshooting Records Management database issues, and suggests programming changes.Assists in the retrieval and refile of files and boxes and from off-site storage locations.Coordinates with Financial Services and Corporate Services departments to set up Access Copyright contract agreement, paying invoices, and preparing cross charges. Liaises with Information Technology Services department to troubleshoot the Copyright Tracking database issues, and suggests programming changes.Supports BCIT’s records custodians (120+) in management of paper records and electronic repositories, manages off-site records program and arranges disposition of records.Provides Records Custodian Advisory Support and maintains authority of control in Custodian stations, provides advice on retention schedules, records management forms and procedures, including life cycle control and disposition of records to ensure legal compliance.Conducts records series inventories such as those relating to personal data collection forms, personal information banks, records series, etc. Provides quality assurance checks prior to sending records off-site for storage.Prepares and delivers one-on-one and group training sessions on records management in-person and online.Maintains current knowledge of records management by keeping up-to-date with current practices and continuing education.Other:Undertakes related duties as assigned, consistent with the job grade for this position.QUALIFICATIONS:Definition:The qualifications section for this position was developed using the approved job evaluation plan, agreed to between the BCGEU and BCIT. The qualifications represent the minimum qualifications required in the future (i.e. to be reflected in job postings) and do not reflect the incumbent’s existing qualifications.Education:Completion of Grade 12, plus completion of a two-year Certified Library and Information Technology Diploma. Requires a certificate in Records Management.License(s)/Certifications(s):Valid Driver’s License and a vehicle for occasional delivery or pick-up.Experience:Two years’ general experience plus up to four years’ practical, current experience in a similar position in a library or records management setting.Software/Computer Application(s) and Expertise:Considerable knowledge of and experience with advanced features of Microsoft Office applications such as Word, Excel, PowerPoint and Outlook.Working knowledge in a variety of software programs, databases, web browsers, web editing software and Adobe Acrobat.Knowledge of and experience with records management systems.Communication/Interpersonal Skills:Excellent organizational, interpersonal, oral and written communication skills.Ability to deal courteously, tactfully, and discretely with clients in a diverse and inclusive environment.Excellent problem-solving and decision-making skills.Administrative Skills (e.g. prioritizing, minute taking, wp speed, etc.):Demonstrated ability to set priorities, manage deadlines and details, coordinate multiple tasks, undertake and monitor project initiatives, while exercising considerable judgment, tact and diplomacy.Ability to maintain confidentiality.High level of accuracy.Other Skills/Abilities:Must be a team player who is customer service oriented, self-directed, responsible and dependable.Demonstrated ability to deal with confidential matters in accordance with accepted professional and ethical standards.Ability to carry out physical requirements of the position, e.g., lifting boxes of up to 35 pounds.Benefits – Why you’d love working with usCompetitive payMinimum of fifteen days of vacationCompetitive employer-paid extended health and dental plan – take a look at our benefit plans!Defined benefit pension plan with employer contributionsFlexible hybrid work arrangements availableProfessional Development funds and resourcesAccess to most BCIT Flexible Learning courses free of chargeWellness and Employee Assistance programsComplimentary membership with free access to the Fitness Centre, Gymnasium, and moreBCIT values diverse experiences, ideas, cultures and perspectives and is committed to fostering a diverse and inclusive workplace. As an equal opportunity employer, we encourage applications from members of all groups experiencing barriers to equity. If you require accessibility accommodations during any part of the application or hiring process, please contact RecruitmentAssistant@bcit.ca so we can best support you. Please note that all applications must be submitted via the careers page portal, email applications will not be accepted.The British Columbia Institute of Technology acknowledges that our campuses are located on the unceded traditional territories of the Coast Salish Nations of xwməθkwəy̓əm (Musqueam), Sḵwx̱wú7mesh (Squamish), and səl̓ilwətaɁɬ (Tsleil-Waututh).To view the full posting, and to apply, please visit: https://careers.bcit.ca/postings/7291 Compensation $54,753 per annum. Closes: 19 September, 2023 British Columbia Institute of Technology Burnaby , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
